# Thread Digest: Experiment 11 Analysis, Experiment 12 Design, and Manuscript Framing

## 1. Thread scope

This thread focused on analyzing **Experiment 11** results for context-separated memory and non-destructive rebinding, using the uploaded Experiment 11 plots, CSVs, logs, and generated report. The analysis then motivated the design and packaging of **Experiment 12**, intended to stress-test capacity, interference, compositional generalization, continual retention, context robustness, and consolidation pressure.

The thread also established the working manuscript frame:

**Title:** `Context-Indexed Structural Plasticity Enables Non-Destructive Rebinding of Compositional Route Memories`

**Subtitle:** `A synthetic route-memory model separates storage, contextual retrieval, and recurrent execution across incompatible worlds`

Experiments 1–10 were referenced only as broader manuscript context. They were not reanalyzed in this thread.

