## 2. Experiments discussed

### Experiment 11 — Context-Separated Memory and Non-Destructive Rebinding

Experiment 11 tested whether higher-order world context can separate multiple route systems over the same source/mode substrate. It measured old-world retention during new-world learning, alternating-world stability, multi-world scaling, and retrieval robustness under world-context bleed/dropout. The uploaded report explicitly defines this purpose and lists the major metrics and generated outputs. 

Main phases discussed:

* sequential A/B learning;
* alternating worlds;
* multi-world scaling across worlds A, B, C, D;
* world-context bleed;
* world-context dropout;
* final sequential failure taxonomy.

