## 10. Relationship to the first manuscript

### Central claim

This thread directly contributes to the central claim:

> Context-indexed structural plasticity enables non-destructive rebinding of compositional route memories across incompatible worlds.

Experiment 11 provides the clearest support by showing that the full and world-gated models preserve A while acquiring B, and scale to multiple worlds, while specific ablations fail in interpretable ways.

### Supporting claim

This thread supports the stronger mechanistic decomposition:

> Structural plasticity stores route structure; world/context binding separates incompatible memories; recurrence executes multi-step routes.

The no-recurrence result is especially important because it separates route-table storage from composed execution.

### Limitation

This thread identifies major manuscript limitations:

* synthetic task;
* lack of novelty search;
* lack of external baselines;
* incomplete capacity scaling;
* insufficient formal statistics;
* consolidation/inhibition not essential in current regime;
* biological claims remain speculative.

